## Common Scenarios

### Scenario 1: Date Handling

Instead of auto-adding moment.js (2.3MB):
-> Present: date-fns (78KB) vs day.js (7KB) vs native

### Scenario 2: Utility Functions

Instead of auto-adding full lodash (70KB):
-> Present: lodash-es (tree-shakeable) vs native methods

### Scenario 3: Form Validation

Instead of auto-adding yup (40KB) + ajv (120KB):
-> Present: zod (50KB total) vs native validation

### Scenario 4: HTTP Client

Instead of auto-adding axios (13KB):
-> Present: native fetch (0KB) vs ky (8KB)
-> Note: For simple cases, fetch is enough

### Scenario 5: State Management

Instead of auto-adding Redux Toolkit (45KB):
-> Present: Zustand (3KB) vs Jotai (5KB) vs Context API (0KB)

### Scenario 6: Cloud Deploy + SQLite (NOVO)

```
User: "Criar app com SQLite, deploy no Railway"

AI: [PARA e mostra alerta de conflito SQLite + Cloud]
AI: "Detectei conflito critico..."
[Aguarda usuario escolher PostgreSQL, Turso, ou mudar deploy]
```

### Scenario 7: Cloud Deploy + Uploads (NOVO)

```
User: "Adicionar upload de imagens, app esta no Vercel"

AI: [PARA e mostra alerta de uploads + Cloud]
AI: "Uploads locais nao persistem no Vercel..."
[Aguarda usuario escolher Cloudinary, S3, ou outra solucao]
```

